quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  28,14,"And when he had attained his full strength and had matured, We gave him wise judgment and knowledge, for thus do We repay thosewho excel in doing good."
  28,15,"And<i class=""s"">(one day) </i>he entered the city unnoticed by its people and found in it two men fighting—one of his own sect and one from his enemies, so the one of his sect solicited his assistance against the one from his enemies, so Moses struck him and put an end to him. He said, “This is of Satan’s work; he is indeed an evidently misguiding enemy.”"
  28,16,"He said, “My Lord, I have indeed been unjust to myself, so forgive me.” So He forgave him; indeed, He is the Oft-Forgiving, the Bestower of mercy."
  28,17,"He said, “My Lord, because of the blessings You have bestowed upon me, I shall not be a backup for criminals.”"
  28,18,"So the next morning he was walking about the city, fearful<i class=""s"">(and) </i>vigilant, when suddenly the man who had sought his support the day before cried out to him. Moses said to him, “You are an evident deluder.”"
  28,19,"And as he was about to strike the one who was their enemy, he said, “O Moses, do you want to kill me as you killed someone yesterday? You only want to be a tyrant in the land and do not want to be of the reformers.”"
  28,20,"And a man came running from the farthest part of the city; he said, “O Moses, the chiefs are conspiring to kill you, so get out; I am indeed one of those who seek to advise you.”"
  28,21,"So he went out of it, fearful<i class=""s"">(and) </i>vigilant; he said, “My Lord, deliver me from the unjust people.”"
